text: Shell Lake High School is a high school in Shell Lake, Wisconsin, in Washburn County, Wisconsin. The school had a separate school called the Shell Lake Primary that educates grades K-2\. In 2018, a local referendum was successfully voted on and passed on the Shell Lake community. This resulted in an expansion on the high school to build classrooms for grades K - 2 and including both a second gymnasium and an auditorium. The Shell Lake Primary School's final year was the 2019/2020 academic year. The final year was cut short in March 2020 due to the COVID19 pandemic thus finishing the remainder of the academic year through online education. ==Sports== Shell Lake High School is Division 3 for most sports of the Wisconsin Interscholastic Athletic Association. Their team name is the Shell Lake Lakers. Shell Lake High School is noted for its football team, which has claimed three state titles. It has also won a state title in team wrestling and girls' track athletics. It was also a state runner-up in baseball. Sports played at Shell Lake High School include:Football, Volleyball (girls only), Basketball, Track and Field, Baseball, Softball, Cross Country, and Wrestling. ==External links== Category:Public high schools in Wisconsin Category:Schools in Washburn County, Wisconsin Category:Public middle schools in Wisconsin Category:Public elementary schools in Wisconsin
